This is where I think Pantheon shifts from being a collection of modules into what could be thought of as a closed-loop learning architecture.

The key idea isn’t that token trajectories reveal hidden truths—they don’t. They reveal the model’s internal semantic tendencies. Those tendencies become one source of evidence that can be combined with external validation.

Here’s how I’d connect it.

